<exploration xml:id="warm-observa-gruposYArreglos" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Observa y pregúntate: Grupos y arreglos</title>

<statement>
  <p>¿Qué observas? ¿Qué te preguntas?</p>
   <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-136262">
        <shortdescription>Grupos de tres puntos negros y azules sobre fondo verde</shortdescription>
      </image>
      <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-136261">
        <shortdescription>Matriz de puntos negros y azules sobre fondo verde</shortdescription>
      </image>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Students may notice:</p>
<ul>
      <li>There are 6 groups of 3 in both diagrams.</li>
      <li>There are 15 black dots and 3 blue dots in each diagram.</li>
      <li>There are 18 dots in both diagrams.</li>
      <li>The first image and the array each have a group of dots that's a different color.</li>
    </ul>
<p>Students may wonder:</p>
<ul>
      <li>Why are some dots a different color?</li>
      <li>What situations could these diagrams represent?</li>
      <li>Why are the dots arranged differently in the 2 images?</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


